-- Spain’s CAF Plans to Cut Jobs in Zaragoza, Economista Reports
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-07-14T14:10:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-14/spain-s-caf-plans-to-cut-jobs-in-zaragoza-economista-reports.html
Construcciones & Auxiliar de
Ferrocarriles SA  plans to put 582 workers at its plant in
Zaragoza,  Spain , which employs about 780 people, on temporary
layoffs because of a decline in railroad activity,  El Economista 
reported, citing the company’s workers council.  CAF expects the slowdown to continue until the first
quarter of 2013 and the employees will be out of work for a
maximum of 51 days, which could be applied within a six-month
period depending on production needs, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  